<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-435-742  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 435 742.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  May 14 1990 n300 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell plots NetWare plans. (integrated resource mgm't coming)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Haight, Timothy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Novell Inc is developing a local area network (LAN) management andmonitor software to provide centralized control especially formultivendor systems.andP;  The new resource management softwareincludes a graphical user interface that indicates problems withicons and lets the LAN manager use a mouse.andP;  The software isdesigned to monitor driver configurations, disk capacity, files inuse, printers, databases and messaging services.andP;  A number ofnetwork management software packages are available but Novellbelieves this NetWare-based product is the first that facilitatesmonitoring of LANs with components from different vendors and thefirst that combines a number of functions into one central controlconsole.andP;  Shipment is planned for the beginning of 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Product:   NetWare (Network operating system) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentNetwork Management SoftwareCentralizationMultivendor SystemsLocal Area NetworksNetwork Monitors.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>